28class TemplateInfo
29 : public TorqueGeneratedTemplateInfo<TemplateInfo, HeapObject> {
30 public:
31 static const int kFastTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize = 1 * KB;
32
33 // While we could grow the slow cache until we run out of memory, we put
34 // a limit on it anyway to not crash for embedders that re-create templates
35 // instead of caching them.
36 static const int kSlowTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize = 1 * MB;
37
38 // If the serial number is set to kDoNotCache, then we should never cache this
39 // TemplateInfo.
40 static const int kDoNotCache = -1;
41 // If the serial number is set to kUncached, it means that this TemplateInfo
42 // has not been cached yet but it can be.
43 static const int kUncached = -2;
44
45 inline bool should_cache() const;
46 inline bool is_cached() const;
47
48 inline bool TryGetIsolate(Isolate** isolate) const;
49 inline Isolate* GetIsolateChecked() const;
50
51 using BodyDescriptor = StructBodyDescriptor;
52
53 // Whether or not to cache every instance: when we materialize a getter or
54 // setter from an lazy AccessorPair, we rely on this cache to be able to
55 // always return the same getter or setter. However, objects will be cloned
56 // anyways, so it's not observable if we didn't cache an instance.
57 // Furthermore, a badly behaved embedder might create an unlimited number of
58 // objects, so we limit the cache for those cases.
59 enum class CachingMode { kLimited, kUnlimited };
60
61 template <typename ReturnType>
62 static MaybeHandle<ReturnType> ProbeInstantiationsCache(
63 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
64 int serial_number, CachingMode caching_mode);
65
66 template <typename InstantiationType, typename TemplateInfoType>
67 static void CacheTemplateInstantiation(
68 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
69 DirectHandle<TemplateInfoType> data, CachingMode caching_mode,
70 Handle<InstantiationType> object);
71
72 template <typename TemplateInfoType>
73 static void UncacheTemplateInstantiation(
74 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
75 DirectHandle<TemplateInfoType> data, CachingMode caching_mode);
76
77 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(TemplateInfo)
78};

92// See the api-exposed FunctionTemplate for more information.
93class FunctionTemplateInfo
94 : public TorqueGeneratedFunctionTemplateInfo<FunctionTemplateInfo,
95 TemplateInfo> {
96 public:
97#define DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(Name, CamelName, Type) \
98 DECL_GETTER(Get##CamelName, Tagged<Type>) \
99 static inline void Set##CamelName( \
100 Isolate* isolate, Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info, \
101 Handle<Type> Name);
102
103 // ObjectTemplateInfo or Undefined, used for the prototype property of the
104 // resulting JSFunction instance of this FunctionTemplate.
105 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(prototype_template, PrototypeTemplate, HeapObject)
106
107 // In the case the prototype_template is Undefined we use the
108 // prototype_provider_template to retrieve the instance prototype. Either
109 // contains an FunctionTemplateInfo or Undefined.
110 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(prototype_provider_template, PrototypeProviderTemplate,
111 HeapObject)
112
113 // Used to create prototype chains. The parent_template's prototype is set as
114 // __proto__ of this FunctionTemplate's instance prototype. Is either a
115 // FunctionTemplateInfo or Undefined.
116 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(parent_template, ParentTemplate, HeapObject)
117
118 // Returns an InterceptorInfo or Undefined for named properties.
119 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(named_property_handler, NamedPropertyHandler, HeapObject)
120 // Returns an InterceptorInfo or Undefined for indexed properties/elements.
121 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(indexed_property_handler, IndexedPropertyHandler,
122 HeapObject)
123
124 // An ObjectTemplateInfo that is used when instantiating the JSFunction
125 // associated with this FunctionTemplateInfo. Contains either an
126 // ObjectTemplateInfo or Undefined. A default instance_template is assigned
127 // upon first instantiation if it's Undefined.
128 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(instance_template, InstanceTemplate, HeapObject)
129
130 // Either a FunctionTemplateInfo or Undefined. If an instance_call_handler is
131 // provided the instances created from the associated JSFunction are marked as
132 // callable.
133 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(instance_call_handler, InstanceCallHandler, HeapObject)
134
135 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(access_check_info, AccessCheckInfo, HeapObject)
136
137 DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS(c_function_overloads, CFunctionOverloads, FixedArray)
138#undef DECL_RARE_ACCESSORS
139
140 DECL_RELAXED_UINT32_ACCESSORS(flag)
141
142 // Begin flag bits ---------------------
143
144 // This FunctionTemplateInfo is just a storage for callback function and
145 // callback data for a callable ObjectTemplate object.
146 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(is_object_template_call_handler)
147
148 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(has_side_effects)
149
150 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(undetectable)
151
152 // If set, object instances created by this function requires access check.
153 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(needs_access_check)
154
155 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(read_only_prototype)
156
157 // If set, do not create a prototype property for the associated
158 // JSFunction. This bit implies that neither the prototype_template nor the
159 // prototype_provoider_template are instantiated.
160 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(remove_prototype)
161
162 // If not set an access may be performed on calling the associated JSFunction.
163 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(accept_any_receiver)
164
165 // This flag is used to check that the FunctionTemplateInfo instance is not
166 // changed after it became visible to TurboFan (either set in a
167 // SharedFunctionInfo or an accessor), because TF relies on immutability to
168 // safely read concurrently.
169 DECL_BOOLEAN_ACCESSORS(published)
170
171 // This specifies the permissable range of instance type of objects that can
172 // be allowed to be used as receivers with the given template.
173 DECL_PRIMITIVE_GETTER(allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start,
174 InstanceType)
175 DECL_PRIMITIVE_GETTER(allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end, InstanceType)
176
177 // End flag bits ---------------------
178
179 inline InstanceType GetInstanceType() const;
180 inline void SetInstanceType(int api_instance_type);
181
182 inline void SetAllowedReceiverInstanceTypeRange(int api_instance_type_start,
183 int api_instance_type_end);
184
185 static Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> GetOrCreateSharedFunctionInfo(
186 Isolate* isolate, Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> info,
187 MaybeHandle<Name> maybe_name);
188
189 static Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> GetOrCreateSharedFunctionInfo(
190 LocalIsolate* isolate, Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> info,
191 Handle<Name> maybe_name) {
192 // We don't support streaming compilation of scripts with natives, so we
193 // don't need an off-thread implementation of this.
194 UNREACHABLE();
195 }
196
197 // Returns parent function template or a null FunctionTemplateInfo.
198 inline Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> GetParent(Isolate* isolate);
199 // Returns true if |object| is an instance of this function template.
200 inline bool IsTemplateFor(Tagged<JSObject> object) const;
201 bool IsTemplateFor(Tagged<Map> map) const;
202 // Returns true if |object| is an API object and is constructed by this
203 // particular function template (skips walking up the chain of inheriting
204 // functions that is done by IsTemplateFor).
205 bool IsLeafTemplateForApiObject(Tagged<Object> object) const;
206 inline bool instantiated();
207
208 bool BreakAtEntry(Isolate* isolate);
209 bool HasInstanceType();
210
211 // Helper function for cached accessors.
212 static base::Optional<Tagged<Name>> TryGetCachedPropertyName(
213 Isolate* isolate, Tagged<Object> getter);
214 // Fast API overloads.
215 int GetCFunctionsCount() const;
216 Address GetCFunction(int index) const;
217 const CFunctionInfo* GetCSignature(int index) const;
218
219 // CFunction data for a set of overloads is stored into a FixedArray, as
220 // [address_0, signature_0, ... address_n-1, signature_n-1].
221 static const int kFunctionOverloadEntrySize = 2;
222
223 // Bit position in the flag, from least significant bit position.
224 DEFINE_TORQUE_GENERATED_FUNCTION_TEMPLATE_INFO_FLAGS()
225
226 // This is a wrapper around |maybe_redirected_callback| accessor which
227 // returns/accepts C function and converts the value from and to redirected
228 // pointer.
229 DECL_EXTERNAL_POINTER_ACCESSORS_MAYBE_READ_ONLY_HOST(callback, Address)
230 inline void init_callback_redirection(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate);
231 inline void remove_callback_redirection(i::IsolateForSandbox isolate);
232
233 template <class IsolateT>
234 inline bool has_callback(IsolateT* isolate) const;
235
236 DECL_PRINTER(FunctionTemplateInfo)
237
238 class BodyDescriptor;
239
240 private:
241 // When simulator is enabled the field stores the "redirected" address of the
242 // C function (the one that's callabled from simulated compiled code), in
243 // this case the original address of the C function has to be taken from the
244 // redirection.
245 // For native builds the field contains the address of the C function.
246 // This field is initialized implicitly via respective |callback|-related
247 // methods.
248 DECL_EXTERNAL_POINTER_ACCESSORS_MAYBE_READ_ONLY_HOST(
249 maybe_redirected_callback, Address)
250
251 // For ease of use of the BITFIELD macro.
252 inline int32_t relaxed_flag() const;
253 inline void set_relaxed_flag(int32_t flags);
254
255 // Enforce using SetInstanceType() and SetAllowedReceiverInstanceTypeRange()
256 // instead of raw accessors.
257 using TorqueGeneratedFunctionTemplateInfo<FunctionTemplateInfo,
258 TemplateInfo>::set_instance_type;
259 DECL_PRIMITIVE_SETTER(allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start,
260 InstanceType)
261 DECL_PRIMITIVE_SETTER(allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end, InstanceType)
262
263 static constexpr int kNoJSApiObjectType = 0;
264 static inline Tagged<FunctionTemplateRareData> EnsureFunctionTemplateRareData(
265 Isolate* isolate, Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info);
266
267 static Tagged<FunctionTemplateRareData> AllocateFunctionTemplateRareData(
268 Isolate* isolate, Handle<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info);
269
270 TQ_OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(FunctionTemplateInfo)
271};
